# Git Workflow Rules

## Branching Strategy

- Always create feature branches from `main`
- Use descriptive branch names: `feature/add-login`, `fix/betting-bug`, `chore/update-deps`

## Commits

- Write clear, concise commit messages
- Use conventional commit format when appropriate: `feat:`, `fix:`, `chore:`, `docs:`, `test:`
- Squash related commits before merging to keep history clean

## Merging to Main

- **ALWAYS use rebase, NEVER merge commits**
- Before creating a PR: `git rebase origin/main`
- When merging PRs: Use "Squash and merge" or "Rebase and merge" (never "Create a merge commit")
- Keep the git history linear and clean

## Pull Requests

- All changes to `main` must go through a PR
- PRs trigger CI checks that must pass before merging
- Squash commits when merging to maintain clean history

## Commands Reference

```bash
# Update your branch with latest main (rebase, not merge)
git fetch origin
git rebase origin/main

# Interactive rebase to squash commits before PR
git rebase -i origin/main

# If you need to force push after rebase (your own branch only)
git push --force-with-lease
```

## Important

- Never force push to `main`
- Never use `git merge` to update feature branches (use `git rebase`)
- Always rebase before creating/updating a PR
